articles.author: Eric Lagatta
articles.title: NASA astronaut Rubio set American record with year-long spaceflight - USA TODAY
articles.description: NASA astronaut Frank Rubio and two Russian cosmonauts landed Wednesday morning after spending 371 days in space, an American record.
articles.content:
• The crew launched Sept. 21, 2022 for what was to be a six-month mission before a coolant leak in their return craft lengthened their stay aboard the space station.
